1
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:08,867
<i> Wait, that's Jalil.</i>

2
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:10,733
<i> When Datu Rahman was arrested,</i>

3
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,767
<i> Jalil suddenly showed up here.</i>

4
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:13,933
<i> And then he was shot!</i>

5
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:15,867
<i>We believe
you are not a bad person.</i>

6
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:18,433
<i>Don't worry,
we will protect you.</i>

7
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> Thank you.</i>

8
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,467
<i>They're still holding
Datu Rahman captive</i>

9
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:23,133
<i>because they need
something from him.</i>

10
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,067
<i> But who are they?</i>

11
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:26,233
<i>And what do they
need from Datu Rahman?</i>

12
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,400
<i> I've examined the bullets.</i>

13
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,233
<i>There's no record of them
in the ballistics database.</i>

14
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:32,533
<i>Whoever abducted Datu Rahman
is part of a larger syndicate.</i>

15
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,267
<i> The guns they used</i>

16
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>are the same smuggled firearms
we've been tracking.</i>

17
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> That's a gunshot wound.</i>

18
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:41,733
<i>Don't forget to file
a police report  within 24 hour.</i>

19
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,967
<i>If you don't,
you will lose your license.</i>

20
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> Did I make the right decision?</i>

21
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:48,300
<i>Am I really helping
an innocent person</i>

22
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,767
<i> or a criminal?</i>

23
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,333
- [TIRES SCREECH]
- [HORN HONKS]

24
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:56,300
<i> Hi, Dad.</i>

25
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> Welcome back, Agent Reyes.</i>

26
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:00,700
Your suspension has been lifted.

27
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:03,467
<i>Your first mission
is to find and arrest</i>

28
00:01:03,467 --> 00:01:05,633
<i>- Datu Rahman's accomplice.
- Yes, sir.</i>

29
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:07,300
<i>I have to keep you
on a short leash.</i>

30
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,933
<i>I need to know
your every move.</i>

31
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:13,733
<i>I finally found someone
to rent this unit!</i>

32
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:15,500
<i> Could you give me a tour?</i>

33
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:19,033
<i>I want to meet
my new neighbors.</i>

34
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,600
<i> Wait, you're that cop!</i>

35
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:21,833
<i>- Oh my.
- Aah!</i>

36
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,367
<i> Come on!
Take one more step!</i>

37
00:01:23,567 --> 00:01:24,700
<i> I dare you!</i>

38
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:36,433
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:46,333
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

40
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,400
No!

41
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,000
We need to stop him.

42
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,067
How?
He's armed.

43
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:56,833
He might shoot us.

44
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,467
There are kids here.

45
00:01:59,433 --> 00:02:02,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:04,233
- Brother!
- Jalil!

47
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:05,567
- Jalil.
- What are you going to do?

48
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:06,733
I have to stop him.

49
00:02:06,733 --> 00:02:09,567
Brother,
your wound is still fresh!

50
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,167
That man can't see you!
He's a cop!

51
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:14,233
If someone gets hurt
because of me,

52
00:02:14,267 --> 00:02:16,300
I will never forgive myself.

53
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,433
- I have to stop him.
- Brother...

54
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:19,733
If he sees you,

55
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,267
you'll put our people
in greater danger

56
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:23,867
because they'll find out
we're hiding you.

57
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:26,767
Your Uncle Omar is right.

58
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:30,400
Everything the people protecting
you have gone through

59
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,833
will be for nothing

60
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:34,533
if you reveal yourself
to that cop!

61
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:38,933
Go on, Jalil.
I'll take care of it.

62
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:40,233
- Be careful.
- Uncle Omar!

63
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:41,433
Jalil.

64
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:48,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:49,467
Jalil!

66
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:50,700
Don't do it.

67
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:52,867
Don't...

68
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,067
Come on!

69
00:02:54,067 --> 00:03:00,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:04,933
We live here in peace.

71
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:09,567
Stop harassing our community.

72
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:14,400
I am looking for this man.

73
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:18,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,033
Hand over the criminal!

75
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:23,833
Weren't you here last night?

76
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:27,367
You didn't see him here.

77
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:29,300
Because you're hiding him!

78
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:33,967
Stop hiding this criminal!

79
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:38,933
Sir, we are not allowed
to harbor fugitives.

80
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:42,600
You're the one
who's causing trouble here.

81
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,400
You're pointing a gun
at unarmed civilians!

82
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:47,167
Leave.

83
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:49,067
We don't want any trouble.

84
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,633
But if you hurt one of us,

85
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:53,633
we'll fight back.

86
00:03:53,633 --> 00:04:00,567
[TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

87
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:03,900
- Get out of here!
- Leave!

88
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:06,133
- Go!
- Get lost!

89
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:08,067
- Leave!
- Get out of our neighborhood!

90
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:11,667
- Go away!
- Leave!

91
00:04:11,667 --> 00:04:12,633
Don't come back!

92
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,467
Whoo!

93
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,633
- Go on.
- Thanks, Mister Omar.

94
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:30,067
These are the candidates
for the new Task Force Alpha.

95
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:31,500
You need to choose four.

96
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:41,633
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,400
What's wrong?

98
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:52,767
Lara, I need to pick
my own team.

99
00:04:52,767 --> 00:04:55,133
I need people I can trust.

100
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:57,867
Like Patrick, Harold,
Russell, Oliver.

101
00:04:57,867 --> 00:04:59,067
You know that!

102
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,700
Okay.

103
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,033
Fair.

104
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:04,100
As for Felix...

105
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:05,900
He's a loose canon.

106
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,233
I can't trust him anymore, Lara.

107
00:05:08,233 --> 00:05:10,967
Look, Felix and I
also don't see eye to eye.

108
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:13,367
But we know his abilities.

109
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:15,933
He has proven himself
over and over.

110
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,033
What happened in Zamboanga
could just be an isolated case.

111
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:23,200
Maybe he really was just
acting in self-defense.

112
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,600
To protect the team.

113
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:28,633
We have to give him
another chance.

114
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:35,600
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:43,800
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,100
[SHOUTS]

117
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,733
You can't hide from me.

118
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:55,900
I will find you.

119
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,533
[EXHALES]

120
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:00,733
I'm going to kill you,
you bastard.

121
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,567
[THUMPING]

122
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,967
Jalil?

123
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:17,833
Brother Jalil,
what are you doing?

124
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,767
Are you leaving?

125
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,100
I can't stay here any longer.

126
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,933
I'm putting all of you
in danger.

127
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,933
But it's not safe!

128
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,800
- Jamilah!
- You are injured!

129
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,933
- Jamilah, stop!
- People are looking for you!

130
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,000
- Jamilah, Jamilah.
- Stop.

131
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:36,800
Jalil!

132
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:39,233
Jamilah is right.

133
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,500
Stay here for now.

134
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,800
That cop won't come back.

135
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,133
They won't stop.

136
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:48,367
I don't want what happened
to our village

137
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:51,267
to happen here.

138
00:06:53,533 --> 00:06:55,800
If something bad
happens to you,

139
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,700
I won't forgive myself.

140
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:01,033
But what about you?

141
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,267
You're not leaving!

142
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,167
- I'm coming!
- Jamilah.

143
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:07,133
- I'm coming with you!
- No, Jamilah!

144
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:12,667
They might think you're
an accomplice too.

145
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,000
You will be safer here.

146
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,700
Stay here.

147
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,600
Auntie.

148
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,633
Let's cool things down first.

149
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:25,700
Let your brother do
what he needs to do.

150
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:31,733
Be careful, brother.

151
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:36,233
Jalil, if you ever
need anything,

152
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,733
don't hesitate
to come back here, okay?

153
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,000
I know we'll all be
together again one day.

154
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:45,700
I'm sorry.

155
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:52,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

156
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,000
Jamilah.

157
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:06,600
Take care of yourself.

158
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,767
Stay safe.

159
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:13,667
Jamilah.

160
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:15,233
[JAMILAH SNIFFLES]

161
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:21,800
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,300
- [SNIFFLES]
- Uncle.

163
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:28,967
Thank you.

164
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,067
Thank you.

165
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:37,900
Sir!

166
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:40,733
You're back.

167
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:45,867
Felix.

168
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,733
We're going to be
working together again.

169
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:52,133
[EXHALES, CLICKS TONGUE]

170
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:53,367
Yes, sir.

171
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,233
It won't happen again.

172
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:58,267
But allow me to apologize, sir.

173
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,900
I panicked back then.

174
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,367
There was a threat to our group.

175
00:09:01,367 --> 00:09:04,400
I was just protecting
our men, sir.

176
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:07,433
[INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

177
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:11,000
Be careful, Felix.

178
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:16,133
Sir, it's them
you should tell to be careful.

179
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:17,767
[LAUGHS]

180
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:29,633
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,833
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

182
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:48,367
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,467
Uh, here, Jalil.

184
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:59,033
It can help with your wound.

185
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,100
I'm sorry...

186
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,967
I didn't know the guy
from earlier

187
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:09,633
was one of the cops
who attacked us last night.

188
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:21,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:23,067
Thank you.

190
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:27,633
By the way,

191
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,433
I cooked some
<i> tiyula itong</i> for you.

192
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:34,167
I know you miss
the food back in Zamboanga.

193
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,600
Here.

194
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:42,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:44,867
Thank you.

196
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,367
Thank you.

197
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:53,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

198
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:59,400
No, it's okay.

199
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,367
- Use it for your travel.
- No, brother.

200
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:02,867
You need it.

201
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,033
Thank you.

202
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:12,800
Thank you.

203
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:16,567
You're going through
a difficult time.

204
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:18,067
Just have faith.

205
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:25,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:11:25,233 --> 00:11:26,900
We'll pray for you.

207
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:51,000
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:15,000
[MUSIC SWELLS, STOPS]

209
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:25,367
We'll be rich, if we
find this criminal, bro!

210
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:28,167
Right. We'll get
two million pesos.

211
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,400
That's not a bad payday.

212
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,033
[MAN LAUGHS]

213
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:37,100
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,467
Omar said you were coming.

215
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:44,167
I owe him a debt of gratitude.

216
00:12:44,367 --> 00:12:45,533
Your timing's perfect.

217
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:47,000
[METAL DOOR RATTLES]

218
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,333
This room's vacant.

219
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,500
Here.

220
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:55,067
I'll leave you to it.

221
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,900
Thank you.

222
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:09,567
- Hmph!
- [SLAMS DOOR]

223
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:21,000
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

224
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:42,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:13:55,100 --> 00:14:02,067
[MUSIC SWELLS]

226
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:25,967
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

227
00:14:25,967 --> 00:14:29,200
<i>You're the leader of the group
that attacked the island</i>

228
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:34,000
<i>and killed my people
before you arrested my father.</i>

229
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,167
[PROTESTER] Justice! Justice!

230
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,667
<i>But when my father
was transferred to prison,</i>

231
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:42,333
<i>you weren't part
of the operation.</i>

232
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,567
<i> You were in civilian clothes</i>

233
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:48,433
<i> and had no NLEA or SID escort.</i>

234
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:53,767
<i>Even at the warehouse,
you went in alone.</i>

235
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:56,100
<i> What happened?</i>

236
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:59,567
<i>Did they target you and
kick you out of the service?</i>

237
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:00,767
<i> Why?</i>

238
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,167
<i> Was it because you were
looking for answers</i>

239
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,167
<i>about the killing
of your teammates?</i>

240
00:15:07,067 --> 00:15:09,633
<i>Who are you really,
Agent Marcus Reyes?</i>

241
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,333
<i> Are you a victim like me?</i>

242
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:20,333
Sir.

244
00:15:20,733 --> 00:15:21,833
Thank you.

245
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:29,200
You're eating well, huh.

246
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,367
You don't use anymore?

247
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:35,967
Sir, I don't!

248
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:38,300
I prayed,

249
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:43,533
"Lord, show me
that You love me!"

250
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:46,700
And He did.

251
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,133
That's why I changed.

252
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,033
You eat a lot, huh?

253
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:54,033
[CHOKES] It's really good, sir.

254
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,067
Uh, wait...

255
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,633
what do you know?

256
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,800
I asked around, sir.

257
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,467
This is from a friend
of my buddy...

258
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,433
He said he saw a van coming
out of the Greenmile warehouse

259
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:15,167
last Monday at around 10 PM.

260
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:18,400
They were speeding.

261
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,500
[HORN HONKS]

262
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,500
He almost got hit.

263
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:26,200
He said there were
a lot of men inside the van.

264
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,567
<i> Hey! Are you trying to die?</i>

265
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:30,000
<i> Watch where you're going!</i>

266
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:31,200
<i> Idiot!</i>

267
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:33,400
<i>- Jerk!
- Idiot!</i>

268
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,400
<i> What's your problem?</i>

269
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:36,767
[SHUTTER CLICKING]

270
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:37,900
[MARCUS] What plate number?

271
00:16:38,233 --> 00:16:39,400
Did he see the plate?

272
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:40,867
It was too fast, sir.

273
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,900
This is all he got.

274
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:51,133
It starts with N
and ends with 475.

275
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,800
This is good enough.

276
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:56,100
Thanks.

277
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,600
[LINE RINGING]

278
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,233
I've got a partial plate number.

279
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:09,467
Bro, imagine this, I was alone.

280
00:17:10,567 --> 00:17:11,900
I didn't even bring a gun.

281
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:13,600
But I took them all down.

282
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,467
Where's Reyes?
Why isn't he here yet?

283
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:19,333
[FELIX] I don't know.
Aren't you two always together?

284
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:21,600
Why are you asking me?
[CHUCKLES]

285
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:25,800
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,800
I have a bad feeling about this.

287
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:34,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:42,567
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

289
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,333
Usman!

290
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:47,933
What are you doing here?

291
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:49,933
I'm also tracking Datu Rahman.

292
00:17:50,467 --> 00:17:53,967
I need to find him to prove
that I didn't let him escape.

293
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,033
I'm talking to the owner
of the van

294
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,367
that was used to transport
Datu Rahman.

295
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,467
[MAN] Good afternoon, sir.

296
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:02,133
Like I said,
I am not guilty.

297
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:03,300
Believe me.

298
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:06,667
My car was stolen
three days ago.

299
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:09,667
I had no idea that it would be
used to commit a crime.

300
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:13,633
Wait, do your cars have
a GPS or a navigation system?

301
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:15,500
Yes, they do.

302
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:20,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:21,700
They haven't removed it yet.

304
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:31,700
[TRACKER BEEPING]

305
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:38,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

306
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:57,000
[TRACKER BEEPING]

307
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:06,367
Brother.

308
00:19:06,867 --> 00:19:07,933
Do you think...

309
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,600
whoever's tailing you won't
be able to follow you here?

310
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,633
We're using your car

311
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:16,200
because they managed
to plant a tracker on mine.

312
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,900
I can't let them follow me.

313
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:21,600
But we still shouldn't
let our guard down.

314
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,067
We don't know what
they're capable of

315
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:24,567
just to keep Datu Rahman hidden.

316
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:31,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:37,033
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

318
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:40,933
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

319
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:47,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,300
Brother.

321
00:19:59,067 --> 00:20:01,133
That's the van.

322
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:05,933
We were right, brother.

323
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:09,300
This is where they brought
Datu Rahman.

324
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:18,000
[PHONE BUZZING]

325
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:29,233
<i>If the massacre on the island
was intentional...</i>

326
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:33,333
<i>the order couldn't have come
from anywhere else but here.</i>

327
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:37,167
<i> I'll find out the truth..</i>

328
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:40,333
<i>You'll all pay for what
you did to my father</i>

329
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:42,300
<i> and to our entire community.</i>

330
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:49,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:00,467
[DOOR OPENS]

332
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:11,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

333
00:21:26,933 --> 00:21:33,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

334
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,100
[DOOR OPENS]

335
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:59,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:05,700
[DOOR KICKS OPEN]

337
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:20,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

338
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,200
There's no one here.

339
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:27,467
This can't be.

340
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:34,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:38,433
[DOOR KICKS OPEN]

342
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:45,900
- [DOOR KICKS OPEN]
- [GROANS LIGHTLY]

343
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:56,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:57,500
[DOOR KICKS OPEN]

345
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:10,467
- [DOOR KICKS OPEN]
- [GROANS LIGHTLY]

346
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:19,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:26,867
[ROPE THROWN]

348
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:28,967
[PHONE RINGING]

349
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:32,033
[RINGING CONTINUES]

350
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:34,833
[RINGING CONTINUES]

351
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:35,700
Lara?

352
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:37,533
Where are you?

353
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,633
I'm here at the
ZylveriX Building.

354
00:23:39,833 --> 00:23:41,800
I've found where
Datu Rahman was taken.

355
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,833
What?! You went alone?

356
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:46,333
[LARA] Didn't I tell you

357
00:23:46,333 --> 00:23:47,767
to let me know
every move you make?

358
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:50,000
What am I doing right now?
I'm telling you, aren't I, Lara?

359
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,867
Marcus, don't get sarcastic
with me!

360
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:53,867
[PHONE THUDS]

361
00:23:53,867 --> 00:24:00,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:24:17,867 --> 00:24:19,700
<i>If you had informed me
right away,</i>

363
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,100
<i> I could have deployed backup.</i>

364
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,733
<i>Lara, the intel came in
all of a sudden.</i>

365
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:24,033
<i>I had no choice
but to move fast.</i>

366
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:25,533
<i> You bypassed me.</i>

367
00:24:25,767 --> 00:24:27,700
<i>And this recklessness
isn't you.</i>

368
00:24:27,867 --> 00:24:29,033
<i> You used to be sharp.</i>

369
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:30,767
<i> Our enemies are cunning.</i>

370
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:34,233
<i>The bullet came from behind,
not from us.</i>

371
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,633
<i>The guns spreading around
are military- and police-grade.</i>

372
00:24:37,633 --> 00:24:38,667
<i> What do you mean?</i>

373
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:44,433
<i>Sir, we have enemies
within NLEA and SID.</i>

374
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:48,033
<i>Why are we hiding
like we're criminals?!</i>

375
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,333
<i> I'll fix this.</i>

376
00:24:49,567 --> 00:24:51,400
<i>But first,
I have to find Father.</i>

377
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:55,233
<i>You, Doctor, will be my way
to get closer to him.</i>

378
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:56,833
<i> To your son Marcus.</i>

379
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:58,500
<i> We're going back to Zylverix.</i>

380
00:24:58,567 --> 00:25:02,133
<i>This is a full-scale search
for Datu Rahman.</i>

381
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:02,933
<i> Move!</i>

382
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:07,033
<i>Angeles, Reyes,
I'm entrusting this to you.</i>

383
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:10,933
<i>Of all people,
why Datu Rahman?</i>

384
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:14,200
Why is there all this bloodshed
<i> just for him?</i>

385
00:25:14,267 --> 00:25:16,500
<i> I have to get inside NLEA.</i>

386
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:18,067
<i>It's the only way
I can think of</i>

387
00:25:18,067 --> 00:25:21,033
<i>to get Father back
as soon as possible.</i>

388
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:22,767
<i> We must recover Datu Rahman</i>

389
00:25:22,767 --> 00:25:26,100
because that is the sole reason
<i> Director Azuelo agreed</i>

390
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:27,967
<i>to my request
to have you reinstated!</i>

391
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:31,133
<i>So who abducted him,
and where is he?!</i>
